1) Crop the target area according to the relative
relationship between the train and the camera (fixed).
2) Detect the position of the train plate using gradients.
3) Binarize the target area and compute both the
horizontal and vertical white pixel accumulation.
4) Separate letters and numbers based on accumulation
information and some prior knowledge.
5) Recognize each box using Tesseract-OCR
(an optical character recognition engine that was developed
at HP Labs between 1985 and 1995 and now at Google).
